The Nigerian Army says a corporal at the Theatre Command Operation Lafiya Dole, Army Super Camp 15, located at Malam Fatori, went berserk in early hours of yesterday, opened fire on and killed four of his colleagues before shooting himself. Army spokesman, Col. Sagir Musa, said two other soldiers were also injured and were currently in stable condition at the Army Hospital in Maiduguri, Borno State Capital. He said efforts were ongoing to contact the families of the gallant colleagues who paid the supreme price in the line of duty. He said investigation into the incident had since been instituted to determine the circumstances that led to the unfortunate incident. Borno: Soldier kills 4 colleagues, injures others Killing of officer, 2 soldiers “wake-up call” for new strategy against terrorism – Buratai Soldier kills 5 colleagues in Philippines